HEADWORD: Intellection
<hw>In`tel*lec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intellectio</ets> synecdoche: cf. F.
<ets>intellection</ets>.]</ety> <def>A mental act or process;</def>
<specif>especially:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The act of understanding;
simple apprehension of ideas; intuition.</def> <au>Bentley</au>.
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A creation of the mind itself.</def>
<rj><au>Hickok.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intellective</ent>⟦br⟧
